commit.message:
Fix help output of suppressed args

Fix help output for suppressed args.
Example:
```
parser.add(
	"--debug",
	env_var="DEBUG",
	action='store_true',
	help=SUPPRESS
)
```
Help output without fix:
```
 --debug                     ==SUPPRESS== [env var: DEBUG]
```

commit.message:
Add ConfigFileParser subclass with pure configparser syntax

- subclass name: ConfigparserConfigFileParser
- allows multi-line values in your config file.
- requires config file to conform to INI file syntax.
- INI sections names still read as comments.

commit.message:
Set COLUMNS=80 in tests to fix failures

The tests rely on specific wrapping of text, so set COLUMNS to enforce
it reliably.

The alternatively would be to make tests accept any wrapping, i.e. any
amounts of whitespace between words and therefore would be more work
for no apparent benefit.

Fixes #146, #163
increment version. Seems like a good time to call this v1.0.
rename open_func to config_file_open_func to be more explicit & consistent with other arg names.
